headlines.description: Harry Kane shook off any World Cup hangover to spark a Tottenham revival in an entertaining 2-2 draw away at Brentford as the Premier League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kane inspires Spurs comeback draw at Brentford

headlines.description: Fulham earned a 3-0 win away to Crystal Palace on Monday to climb to eighth in the Premier League after the hosts had two players sent off.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fulham ease past nine-man Crystal Palace

headlines.description: — Wolverhampton manager Julen Lopetegui marked his Premier League debut with a dramatic stoppage-time 2-1 win at Goodison Park on Monday which ramped up the pressure on Everton coach Frank Lampard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late goal gives Lopetegui winning league start with Wolves

headlines.description: Newcastle's Joelinton won a penalty and netted a header in a 3-0 thrashing of Leicester that took his side up to second in the Premier League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newcastle outclass Leicester to climb to second

headlines.description: Brighton climbed to sixth in the Premier League standings after they won 3-1 away to Southampton on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brighton ease past Southampton as Solly March strikes stunner

headlines.description: — Liverpool extended its winning streak in the Premier League by beating Aston Villa 3-1 on Monday to close the gap on the top four.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liverpool eyes CL spots with 3rd straight league win

headlines.description: — Eddie Nketiah scored the final goal of the match on his first start for Arsenal this season as the Premier League leaders completed a 3-1 comeback win over West Ham on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nketiah scores, leader Arsenal rallies to beat West Ham 3-1
